JOHANNESBURG - Legendary South African ultra-marathon runner Bruce Fordyce was held up and robbed while on a morning run in Westcliff, Johannesburg on Friday morning.While running this am I was assaulted and held up at gun point by thugs. stole my shoes, watch. Stumbled home fresh shoes, finished my runThe celebrated athlete was reportedly attacked after an unknown vehicle with armed individuals pulled up alongside him and held him up at gunpoint.The 61-year-old was robbed of his running shoes and wrist watch.READ: Atletico's Koke robbed at gunpoint for 70k watch The odds were stacked against me because he had a gun and if I could I would want a rematch Fordyce told TimesLIVE.Fordyce won the Comrades Marathon nine times between 1980 and 1990. eNCA